On Jun 7, 2006, at 4:25 PM, Cliff Rhoton wrote:

>  My `78 2.0 Litre motor was
> said to be Aluminum.  Is it in reality a magnesium
> alloy like the bug motor instead?

Modern T1 cases are made from an alloy of Magnesium.

AS21 - Mg Al2 Si which means Magnesium alloyed with up to 2% Aluminum  
and 1% Silicon
AS41 - Mg Al4 Si, up to 4% Al

T4 cases are made from an alloy of Aluminum. My guess is that they  
also contain Si and Mg because it's common to do.

